just_use beginner_corpus.py

# label: TOOL
# role: deterministic corpus runner for beginner.py before/after testing

Hand-crafted (name, board, trouble_card) triples — distinct
from the random-deal corpus in `corpus/sessions.txt`. Runs
`beginner_plan` against every entry and prints a stable
report `name : depth : verb1 / verb2 / ... / verbN` (or
`STUCK`) plus a final depth distribution.

Output is deterministic across runs of the same beginner.py.
Pipe to a file and `git diff` to compare runs.

```
python3 beginner_corpus.py            # print
python3 beginner_corpus.py > out.txt  # snapshot
```

## Pointers

- Companion to `bfs_solver.py`'s `corpus_report.py` — the
  `bfs_solver` side reads from the random-deal sessions DB,
  this one ships its own hand-built fixtures.
